
The World Health Organization estimates about 18 million people around the
globe suffer from Alzheimer's Disease, a degenerative disease in which brain
cells whither away and die.  Wednesday May 14 in Washington, former Supreme
Court Justice Sandra Day O'Connor told the Senate Special Committee on Aging
more can, and must be done for victims of the disease and those caring for
them.   VOA's Paul Sisco reports.
 
 
